import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String javadoc = """
/**
 * Returns a predicated (validating) queue backed by the given queue.
 * <p>
 * Only objects that pass the test in the given predicate can be added to the queue.
 * Trying to add an invalid object results in an IllegalArgumentException.
 * It is important not to use the original queue after invoking this method,
 * as it is a backdoor for adding invalid objects.
 *
 * @param <E> the type of the elements in the queue
 * @param queue  the queue to predicate, must not be null
 * @param predicate  the predicate used to evaluate new elements, must not be null
 * @return a predicated queue
 * @throws NullPointerException if the queue or predicate is null
 */
""";

        Map<String, String> throwsMap = generateThrows(javadoc);
        for (Map.Entry<String, String> entry : throwsMap.entrySet()) {
            System.out.println("{" +
                    "description: \"" + entry.getValue() +
                    "\", " +
                    "assertion: \"assert " + entry.getKey().replace("_", "\\_") + ";\", " +
                    "name: \"" + entry.getKey() + "\", " +
                    "content: \"" + entry.getValue() + "\"}");
        }
    }

    public static Map<String, String> generateThrows(String javadoc) {
        // Split the Javadoc into lines
        String[] lines = javadoc.split("\n");

        // Initialize a map to store the @throws tags
        Map<String, String> throwsMap = new HashMap<>();

        // Iterate over each line in the Javadoc
        for (String line : lines) {
            // Check if the line starts with "@throws"
            if (line.startsWith("@throws")) {
                // Extract the exception name and description from the @throws tag
                int index = line.indexOf("(");
                String exceptionName = line.substring(index + 1, line.length() - 1).split(",")[0].trim();
                String description = line.substring(line.lastIndexOf(":") + 2);

                // Remove any HTML tags from the description
                description = description.replaceAll("<.*?>", "");

                // Add the exception name and description to the map
                throwsMap.put(exceptionName, description);
            }
        }

        return throwsMap;
    }
}
```

This program first splits the Javadoc into lines. Then it iterates over each line in the Javadoc. If a line starts with "@throws", it extracts the exception name and description from the @throws tag. The description is then cleaned up by removing any HTML tags. Finally, the exception name and description are added to a map.

The program then prints out the generated assertion statements for each @throws tag in the map.
